30|$|Lastly, {{some authors}} report an ionospheric east–west {{difference}} in {{both sides of}} the longitudes with zero magnetic declination (Zhang et al. 2011; Xu et al. 2013; Zhao et al. 2013), hereafter named longitudinal anomaly. They suggested that this longitudinal anomaly is caused by the difference in magnetic declination that gives rise to upward and downward <b>ion</b> <b>drifts</b> across the zero declination for a given thermospheric zonal wind direction.|$|R
